From af6e76207e5ba1cd3b45ae05d9729237f34bc040 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Shrikanth Hegde <sshegde@linux.ibm.com>
Date: Thu, 15 Jan 2026 13:05:23 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] sched/fair: Change likelyhood of nohz.nr_cpus

References: bsc#1234634, bsc#1258961
Patch-mainline: v7.0-rc1
Git-commit: 94e70734b4d034b9df795bd1ad3452ea96e742ca

These days most of the system have multi cores. The likelyhood of
at least one or more CPUs in nohz (idle state) is higher.

Give accurate hint to the branch predictor.

Reviewed-and-tested-by: K Prateek Nayak <kprateek.nayak@amd.com>
Signed-off-by: Shrikanth Hegde <sshegde@linux.ibm.com>
Signed-off-by: Peter Zijlstra (Intel) <peterz@infradead.org>
Reviewed-by: Vincent Guittot <vincent.guittot@linaro.org>
Link: https://patch.msgid.link/20260115073524.376643-3-sshegde@linux.ibm.com
Signed-off-by: Mel Gorman <mgorman@suse.de>
---
 kernel/sched/fair.c | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/kernel/sched/fair.c b/kernel/sched/fair.c
index e0eb603ea96e..b8a78ecc0af5 100644
--- a/kernel/sched/fair.c
+++ b/kernel/sched/fair.c
@@ -12548,9 +12548,9 @@ static void nohz_balancer_kick(struct rq *rq)
 
 	/*
 	 * None are in tickless mode and hence no need for NOHZ idle load
-	 * balancing:
+	 * balancing
 	 */
-	if (likely(!atomic_read(&nohz.nr_cpus)))
+	if (unlikely(!atomic_read(&nohz.nr_cpus)))
 		return;
 
 	if (rq->nr_running >= 2) {
